"Meurisse M., Van Vliet-Lanoë B., Talon B., Recourt P.","Holocene dune and peat complexes along the shore of northern France [Complexes dunaires et tourbeux holocènes du littoral du Nord de la France]",2005,"Comptes Rendus - Geoscience","337","7",,"675","684",,,10.1016/j.crte.2005.02.009,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-18144396212&partnerID=40&md5=d3527a5283972849cdd95e7d5c614e9c","UMR 8110 PBDS, UFR Sciences de la Terre, Université des Sciences et Technologies de Lille, 59655 Villeneuve-d'Ascq Cedex, France; UMR 6116, Institut Méditerranéen d'Écologie et de Paléoécologie, Faculté des Sciences et Technologies Saint-Jérôme, Av. Escadrille-Normandie-Niemen, 13397 Marseille Cedex 20, France","Meurisse, M., UMR 8110 PBDS, UFR Sciences de la Terre, Université des Sciences et Technologies de Lille, 59655 Villeneuve-d'Ascq Cedex, France; Van Vliet-Lanoë, B., UMR 8110 PBDS, UFR Sciences de la Terre, Université des Sciences et Technologies de Lille, 59655 Villeneuve-d'Ascq Cedex, France; Talon, B., UMR 6116, Institut Méditerranéen d'Écologie et de Paléoécologie, Faculté des Sciences et Technologies Saint-Jérôme, Av. Escadrille-Normandie-Niemen, 13397 Marseille Cedex 20, France; Recourt, P., UMR 8110 PBDS, UFR Sciences de la Terre, Université des Sciences et Technologies de Lille, 59655 Villeneuve-d'Ascq Cedex, France","This survey of the coastal dunes of northern France is based on stratigraphy, 14C dating, sedimentology and morphology applied for palaeoclimatic and palaeodynamic purpose. The dunes rest on a Flandrian prism sealed by Atlantic peats grown backward from a subboreal dune ridge. Two historical building phases are recorded: the late Roman dunes and the 13th century dunes. These events are separated by pedogenesis. Contribution of reworked fluvial sands also records the recent climatic degradation, with an increased storminess (Little Ice Age) associated with more efficient erosion (soil erosion and floods). The dunes of Picardy also record the Global Warming: their morphologies attest a shift from parabolic into longitudinal, by coupling storminess and sea-level rise. © 2005 Académie des sciences. Publié par Elsevier SAS. Tous droits réservés.","Aeolian activity; Climate; Dune; High-resolution stratigraphy; Holocene; Peat","coastal landform; dune; Holocene; paleoclimate; Eastern Hemisphere; Eurasia; Europe; France; Western Europe; World; Roman",,,,,,"Baeteman, C., De Gans, W., Quaternary shorelines in Belgium and the Netherlands (1993), p. 80. , (The Western Belgian coastal dunes) International Union for Quaternary Research (INQUA), Subcommission on shoreline in EuropeBattiau-Queney, Y., Fauchois, J., Deboudt, P., Lanoy-Ratel, P., Beach-dune systems in a macrotidal environment along the northern French coast (2000) J. Coast. Res., pp. 580-592. , English Channel and southern North Sea; Briquet, A., Le littoral du Nord de la France et son évolution morphologique (1930), Paris: Armand ColinChorley, R.J., Schumm, S.A., Sudgen, D.E., (1984) Geomorphology, , London: Methuen & Co. Ltd; Clarke, M., Rendell, H., Tastet, J.-P., Clavé, B., Massé, L., Late-Holocene sand invasion and North Atlantic storminess along the Aquitaine Coast, southwest France (2002) The Holocene, 12 (2), pp. 231-238; Gandouin, E., Enregistrement paléoclimatique de la transgression holocène; signature paléoenvironnementale des Chironomidae (diptères) du bassin de Saint-Omer (2003), (France), thèse, université Lille-1Hack, J.T., Dunes of the western Navajo country (1941) Geogr. Rev., 31, p. 260. , fig. 19; Jelgersma, S., Van der Valk, J.F., An outline of geological history of the coastal dunes in the western Netherlands (1969) Geol. Mijnbouw, 48, pp. 335-342; Jelgersma, S., Sea-level changes in the North Sea basin (1979) Acta Univ. Ups. Symp. Univ. Ups. Annum Quingenteseimum Celebrantis, 2, pp. 233-248. , E. Oele, R.T.E. Schüttenhelm, A.J. Wiggers (Eds.) The Quaternary History of the North Sea; Jelgersma, S., Stive, M.J.F., Van der Valk, L., 